{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \"pwd && sed -n '1,220p' /home/mihailo/.codex/skills/fix-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md && printf '\\\\n---\\\\n' && rg -n \\\"org\\\\.projectlombok:lombok:1\\\\.18\\\\.20|projectlombok|lombok\\\" .\"","aggregated_output":"/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1559-595c12b4\n---\nname: fix-reachability-metadata\ndescription: Fix missing GraalVM reachability metadata for a specific library by reproducing failing tests, extracting missing JSON entries from MissingReflectionRegistrationError output, adding or merging entries in the correct metadata file, inferring missing condition fields from stacktrace package affinity, and rerunning tests until they pass. Use when the user asks to fix or fulfill metadata because the agent did not find required metadata and tests or native-image runs fail with missing metadata errors.\n---\n\n# Fix Reachability Config\n\n## Overview\n\nRun a tight reproduce-fix-verify loop for missing metadata errors. Keep running the target test until it passes with no new missing metadata entries.\n\n- Library coordinates should be provided in the prompt in the format `group:artifact:version`. If you are not sure what the coordinates are, ask the user.\n- Target metadata directory under `metadata/` where updates should be written.\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. Reproduce the failure:\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` from repository root.\n2. Capture the missing metadata payload:\n   - Locate `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`.\n   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type/member.\n3. Choose the target file and insert the entry:\n   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\n   - Keep valid JSON and avoid duplicating an existing equivalent entry. If the type already exists but a method or field is missing, add only that method or field.\n4. Add the missing `condition` field:\n   - Infer it from the error stacktrace.\n   - Set `condition { \"typeReached\": \"<class>\" }` to the first stack trace class whose package shares the leading package namespace with the missing type.\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\n   - If no such class exists, use the first class from a stack trace whose package matches with the provided library group. Package overlapping logic can be partial as well.\n   - Example: missing type `org.hibernate.id...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\n   \n5. Verify and iterate:\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\n\n## Error Patterns\n\nUse this reference when deriving missing entry and condition.\n\n### Missing Reflection Entry Pattern\n\nExample error shape:\n\n```text\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\n...\nadd the following to ... reachability-metadata.json:\n{\n  \"type\": \"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\",\n  \"methods\": [{ \"name\": \"<init>\", \"parameterTypes\": [] }]\n}\n...\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\n```\n\n### Condition Inference\n\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\n\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\n\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\n\n## Environment Troubleshooting\n\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\n\n---\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/lombok-1.18.20-sources.jar\",\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/projectlombok/lombok\",\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/projectlombok/lombok/tree/v1.18.20/test\",\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/lombok-1.18.20-javadoc.jar\",\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/index.json:14:      \"lombok\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:5:        \"typeReached\": \"lombok.permit.Permit\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:11:        \"typeReached\": \"lombok.patcher.ScriptManager\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:26:        \"typeReached\": \"lombok.permit.Permit\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:32:        \"typeReached\": \"lombok.launch.AnnotationProcessorHider$AnnotationProcessor\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:38:        \"typeReached\": \"lombok.core.SpiLoadUtil$1$1\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:40:      \"type\": \"lombok.bytecode.PoolConstantsApp\",\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:50:        \"typeReached\": \"lombok.core.SpiLoadUtil$1$1\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:52:      \"type\": \"lombok.bytecode.PostCompilerApp\",\n./metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json:62:        \"typeReached\": \"lombok.launch.Agent\"\n./metadata/org.projectlombo