{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"reasoning","text":"**Evaluating test project approaches**\n\nI’m considering how to run the test project using a Java agent since the tests already exist. It might be easier to run JVM tests with specific configurations on Gradle. The user only asked for fixes, so I could infer the necessary classes but crafting predefined class configurations seems tricky. I wonder if it's worth inspecting the documentation online. I need to check the full failure stack for MainTest to understand the classes that are causing issues."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_45","type":"reasoning","text":"**Considering class definition issues**\n\nI'm pondering if the Agent, AnnotationProcessor, or PatchFixes might use `Class.forName(..., false, scl)`, which probably tries to define classes and can lead to an UnsupportedFeatureError. Right now, the failure is due to missing resources, but once those are added, I might encounter more UnsupportedFeatureErrors. It looks like I'll need predefined classes or perhaps find another workaround to address these issues effectively."}}
